  "texts": [
    "These terms relate to the scholarly endeavours that have leveraged GeoGebra as an exploratory instrument for geometrical constructs, the visual representation of mathematical concepts and the intricate analysis of various functions, including those of a complex nature.",
    "In recent years, from 2020 to 2023, the integration of GeoGebra in mathematics education has given rise to innovative terms indicative of emerging pedagogical trends.",
    "Noteworthy lexical items include terms such as \"modelling\", \"augmented reality\", \"3D printing\", \"project-based learning\" and \"STEAM\" (an acronym for Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts and Mathematics) \"flipped learning\", \"perception\", \"mathematical discourse\", \"cycle model\" and \"TPACK\" (Technological Pedagogical Content Knowledge), along with \"self-efficacy\", \"problem-solving skills\" and \"mathematical communication\".",
    "These terms suggest a synergy between GeoGebra and advanced technology-driven teaching methods, as well as state-of-the-art pedagogical practices, in addition, they underscore GeoGebra's role in promoting learner-centric educational approaches and enhancing active participation in mathematical investigation.",
    "In summary, from the temporal sequence of the published works in Figure 4, it is noted that the development in the appearance of terms related to the use of GeoGebra in mathematics research can be categorized into three distinct periods."
